# üõ°Ô∏è SecureShop ‚Äì Secure E-Commerce Demo (CYSEC Assignment)

**SecureShop** is a Django-based e-commerce web application built to demonstrate
**secure coding practices**, **authentication hardening**, and **defensive web development**.

Developed for the *CYSEC Assignment (INT6005CEM)*, this project implements an intentionally small
e-commerce site with **strong security features** layered throughout.

---

## üöÄ Features

### üß© Core Functionality
- User registration & login
- Email 2-step verification (6-digit code)
- Product listing, creation, and editing (admin only)
- Shopping cart with checkout
- Order history per user
- File upload for product images

### üîê Security Enhancements
| Security Feature | Description |
|------------------|-------------|
| **CSRF Protection** | All forms use Django‚Äôs built-in CSRF middleware |
| **Session Management** | Sessions are rotated at login; cart stored server-side |
| **Rate Limiting Middleware** | Prevents brute-force attacks on login/register |
| **Honeypot Field** | Stops bots from auto-submitting the registration form |
| **Content Security Policy (CSP)** | Mitigates XSS by restricting allowed sources |
| **Referrer & Permissions Policies** | Limits browser data leakage |
| **HTTPS / HSTS Ready** | Settings prepared for secure production deployment |
| **Audit Logging** | Security-relevant events (login, logout, orders) logged to `audit.log` |
| **Email One-Time Code (2FA)** | Adds step-up authentication after password login |
| **Object-Level Access Control** | Users can only see their own orders |

---

## üß± Tech Stack

- **Backend:** Django 5.x (Python 3.13)
- **Frontend:** Bootstrap 5 via CDN
- **Database:** SQLite (default, switchable to PostgreSQL/MySQL)
- **Logging:** Python logging with file output
- **Email Backend:** Console (development) ‚Äî prints codes to terminal

